Minister of Sport and Recreation South Africa, Min T.W Nxesi congratulates Gift Ngoepe who learned all his baseball skills whilst practicing in a wooden clubhouse in Randburg.&nbsp;"Gift Ngoepe remains the first black South African to sign a professional baseball contract despite hardships and challenges that he grew up experiencing as a young black South African. As South Africans we are indeed proud of him as he remains a beacon of hope to our youth indicating that being selfless, resilient and dedicated remains the best ingredient for success. We hope that his achievement will serve as motivation to the youth to always strive to achieve more" Indicated Min T.W Nxesi.&nbsp;Ngoepe is the first South African to play in the U.S Major League.&nbsp;